==Latin==
===Etymology===
Greek ''[[-ικος]]'', akin to English ''[[-ish]]'', German ''[[-isch]]'', and various suffixes in other Indo-European languages.

===Adjective Suffix===
'''-icus''' ''m'', '''[[-ica]]''' ''f'', '''[[-icum]]''' ''n''

# of or pertaining to; adjective suffix appended to various words to turn them into adjectives.

====Examples====


{|
|-----
| amare || [[amicus]]
|-----
| Gallia || [[gallicus]]
|-----
| unus || [[unicus]]
|}

